# --- Frontend (Vite) — copy to .env for local overrides ---

#

# Local dev: leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset → browser calls /api → Vite proxies to Express (vite.config.js).

#

# Production: set VITE_API_BASE_URL at build time to your API (must end with /api), e.g.:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://xxxx.up.railway.app/api
#
# Express must set FRONTEND_URL / CORS for your live site origin(s).

#

# Dev proxy: Vite reads server/.env PORT and proxies /api to http://localhost:<PORT> (override if needed).

# VITE_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:5002

